                        "difficultyIds": "a0f7d178f7b728b8bba7ef20ddeca62d",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Evaluating 评价",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nLiver and other organ meats would be omitted from the diet of a client who has gout because of their high purine content. Purines are a form of protein. The food items identified in the other options contain negligible amounts of purines and may be consumed freely by the client with gout.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nNote the strategic words, needs additional teaching. These words indicate a negative event query and the need to select the incorrect statement. Focus on the pathophysiology of the client's diagnosis and on the foods high in purine. Remember that organ meats are high in purines.",
