                        "type": "1",
                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "Which tests can be used to diagnose gout? Select all that apply.",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nDiagnostic tests for gout include serum uric acid level and 24-hour urine uric acid level, as well as synovial fluid aspiration and x-ray of the affected areas. Renal ultrasound, bone marrow biopsy, and urinalysis with culture are not specifically associated with gout; they test for a variety of other conditions.\n\nTest-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, tests for gout. Recall the association of uric acid and gout and that uric acid builds up in the joints to assist in directing you to the correct options.",
